== bash mood: an unset variable is an error, not a silent zero:
shit: 1:1: error: The variable 'das' is not set.
     1 |  das
       |  ^~~ here.
== bash mood: a name=value binding recomputes lazily on each read:
7
== sh mood: the same unset error applies:
shit: 1:1: error: The variable 'nope' is not set.
     1 |  nope
       |  ^~~~ here.
== bash mood wraps the overflow to 64 bits:
-9223372036854775808
== the default mood keeps the full 128-bit value:
9223372036854775808
